body_html:
I tried to reproduce and ended up with a different error with 9b69ec3 checked out, but don't see errors on the latest 0.10 release.

In general I would recommend using an official release, rather than an arbitrary commit. FYI the 9b69ec3 commit was on June 6.

Here are instructions on downloading a binary distribution:
https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.10/get_started/os_setup.html#download-and-setup

For source installs, you can use the git clone -b flag to pick a branch. E.g. the following will clone the latest 0.10 release:

$ git clone -b v0.10.0rc0 https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow

Hope this helps! Please re-open if you still encounter issues on an official release.

Here are instructions on downloading a binary distribution:
https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.10/get_started/os_setup.html#download-and-setup
